Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.06,0:00:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What do you think you're doing, snatching me from the street without so much as a by-your-leave?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.12,0:00:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been a secret admirer of yours \Nfor some time, my dear Waver Velvet.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.10,0:00:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And who in blazes are you supposed to be?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.44,0:00:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Reines El-Melloi Archisorte.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.90,0:01:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,If I said I was the sister, by succession, of Kayneth El-Melloi Archibald,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.70,0:01:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,participant in the Fourth Holy Grail War \Nand your former professor, would that ring a bell?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.42,0:01:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm his niece, if we're speaking strictly in terms of bloodlines.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.30,0:01:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So you brought me here for—
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.62,0:01:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Perish the thought. I have no interest in vulgar things like revenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.80,0:01:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I merely wished to ask you a question \Nthat's been on my mind for some time.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.10,0:01:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You were a participant in the ritual conducted in Fuyuki City
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.26,0:01:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to summon an omnipotent, \Nwish-granting Grail,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.00,0:01:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Holy Grail War \Nto determine who would claim it, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.04,0:01:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I was.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.90,0:01:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Where my brother lost both the War and his life, and brutally at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.90,0:01:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I met defeat as well. \NFortunately, my life was spared.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.16,0:01:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't be so quick to call that fortunate, but let us move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.92,0:01:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Six months ago, you returned to England, \Nborrowed enough money to put you deeply in debt,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.06,0:02:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and purchased the right to operate the \NEl-Melloi Classroom my brother left behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.88,0:02:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see me as a thief who made off \Nwith his mentor's legacy?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.72,0:02:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Not in the slightest! As a professor, \Nyou're spoken of quite highly, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.80,0:02:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,However, I am quite curious about what motivated you to do all this.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.48,0:02:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a right to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.45,0:02:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.14,0:02:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's quite a long story.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.77,0:02:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd best shorten it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.22,0:02:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I hear the human body can't endure \Nbeing suspended upside-down for long.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.08,0:02:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,There's some debate as to the exact length of time required,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.72,0:02:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,but after about three hours, the strain of circulating blood in reverse becomes too great,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.48,0:02:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and the heart simply stops beating.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.64,0:02:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I get the picture!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.23,0:02:48.25,Default,chptr,0,0,0,,{Episode}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.90,0:03:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is Babylon.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.40,0:03:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The city built by Gilgamesh, first of kings,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.46,0:03:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and the place where Iskandar, \Nconqueror of all the world, met his end.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.68,0:03:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.44,0:03:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Curse you!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.42,0:03:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Move, you piece of scrap!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.20,0:03:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got to get to the doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.12,0:03:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.24,0:03:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't get this junk heap to start!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.46,0:03:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it all!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.74,0:04:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,He told me it was made in Japan!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.56,0:04:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.72,0:04:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.00,0:04:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry. This was his city, once.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.32,0:04:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the least I can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.02,0:04:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as I thought. The spark plug's done for.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.80,0:04:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You only need it to get you \Nas far as the doctor's, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.92,0:04:21.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.08,0:04:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.30,0:04:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In that case...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.10,0:04:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,For real?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.42,0:04:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Will that do?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.68,0:04:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.22,0:04:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just a temporary fix, mind. \NBe sure to keep the engine running.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.94,0:04:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,On your way to the doctor, \Ngo buy a new spark plug!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.14,0:04:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I owe you one, tourist dude!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.68,0:04:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi there. You're clearly a magus.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.48,0:04:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.04,0:04:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.84,0:05:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,These are...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.56,0:05:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Mystic Eyes of Binding!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.68,0:05:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I hail from the Clock Tower, myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.92,0:05:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The locals all know me as Barzan, the London boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.92,0:05:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm kind of a big deal around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.66,0:05:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Never heard of you. I'm just looking for somewhere to spend the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.64,0:05:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't come here for a class reunion.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.22,0:05:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a combination of my Mystic Eyes and conditional magecraft I put on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.50,0:05:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Ain't that impressive, my dear underclassman?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.72,0:05:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I've seen better.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.30,0:05:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So you need a place for the night? \NCome stay at mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.54,0:05:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Sound good?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.26,0:05:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you go! This here's the guest room.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.08,0:05:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's no three-star hotel, but go on and make yourself comfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.88,0:05:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.60,0:05:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The body of a magus makes for excellent raw materials.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.42,0:05:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be making full use of yours, \Nso don't wear it out too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.32,0:05:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,As a living sacrifice, you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.70,0:05:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So long, my little underclassman.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.56,0:06:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll send down some room service later.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.06,0:06:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Go to hell!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.18,0:06:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Couldn't cut it in London so you came here to strut around like a big shot, huh, you wanker?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.98,0:06:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.76,0:06:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Calm down, damn you!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.16,0:06:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The Mystic Eyes' effects are long spent!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.70,0:06:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Which means this is nothing more than a rudimentary barrier!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.64,0:06:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you please keep it down?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.76,0:06:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Put a bloody cork in it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.58,0:06:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-You're...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.88,0:06:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Waver?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.96,0:06:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Waver Velvet! Is it really you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.48,0:06:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Melvin?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.64,0:06:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The very same!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.18,0:06:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's me! Your old school chum, Melvin Waynes!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.60,0:06:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't possibly be happier to see you!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.46,0:06:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep that away from me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.90,0:07:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You never did stop the whole \N"vomiting up blood without warning" thing, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.14,0:07:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But what are you {\i1}doing{\i0} here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.68,0:07:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,A chap from school said it was the perfect place to seek my fortune,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.85,0:07:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,so I got on a flight, and next thing I knew I was in here!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.94,0:07:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That must have been that Barzan scumbag.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.76,0:07:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I was so looking forward to meeting some lovely Arabian ladies,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.73,0:07:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,but instead of my own 1,001 Nights, he just took my 30,000,000 dollars.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.60,0:07:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You're one sad bastard, Melvin.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.70,0:07:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What kind of way is that to talk to an old friend?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.78,0:07:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't recall us ever being friends in the first place!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.38,0:07:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, so that's how it is?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.74,0:07:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,After you borrowed all that money from me to go to Japan?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.34,0:07:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.76,0:07:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Melvin! Wait up!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.04,0:07:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard that you'll pay any price for an interesting story.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.54,0:07:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right! If it's a really good tale, \Nno sum of my mum's money is too great!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.98,0:07:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Then pay for me to go to Japan!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.74,0:08:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Japan?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.32,0:08:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to turn this moldy old Clock Tower upside down!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.66,0:08:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's hear that interesting story you promised.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.56,0:08:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,How did you find Japan?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.02,0:08:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd be able to lay your head in the \Nfinest geisha's lap with the sum I gave you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.36,0:08:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry. It's not that kind of story.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.86,0:08:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.64,0:08:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I entered that Holy Grail War, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.34,0:08:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I was completely useless.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.14,0:08:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold your horses. So the stories you were planning to tell me were of this Holy Grail War?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.32,0:08:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.32,0:08:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But I suspect you already know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.92,0:08:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,There were rumors going around that \NProfessor Kayneth died like a dog over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.18,0:08:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So you didn't know that my uncle had died.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.82,0:08:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The Holy Grail War ended with no winner, \Nso it was hard to believe he'd still be alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.22,0:08:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I suppose you had no way of knowing for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.71,0:08:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,His fiancée Sola-Ui was killed along with him, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.60,0:09:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Their corpses were in a terrible state, I heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.72,0:09:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Barely anything was left to be salvaged of their magic crests.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.02,0:09:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Such a terrible waste.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.28,0:09:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody murdered him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.90,0:09:15.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the Saber-class Heroic Spirit, apparently.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.46,0:09:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this business about summoning great figures \Nfrom history and using them as familiars really true?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.88,0:09:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the Holy Grail War in a nutshell.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.96,0:09:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,A battle to the death between legendary heroes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.40,0:09:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's get out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.08,0:09:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Waver?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.68,0:09:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't plan to stay here a second longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.04,0:09:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Knocking down the door by accelerating the natural aging of the hinges! What a fabulous idea!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.06,0:09:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no need to destroy it with brute strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.60,0:09:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,When you discard your preconceptions,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.72,0:09:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll find all sorts of alternatives open up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.46,0:09:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You've changed a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.64,0:09:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You finally get your v-card stamped?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.60,0:10:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I did no—
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.45,0:10:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, {\i1}do{\i0} go on!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.50,0:10:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So, did you or didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.94,0:10:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That has no relevance to this story whatsoever!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.08,0:10:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, as we traversed deeper into the tunnels, \Nwe reached his workshop.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.62,0:10:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.70,0:10:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that. He's been feeding \Nthe locals a bunch of lies
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.64,0:10:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to con them into digging up \Nthe ruins of Babylon for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.54,0:10:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems this could be where the tomb of Iskandar lies.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.26,0:10:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as well for us that the excavation is keeping them busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.92,0:10:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Time to make our escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.60,0:10:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.32,0:10:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I said we should get out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.62,0:10:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Not that bit! Where did you say this is?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.00,0:10:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Like I said, it could be Iskandar's tomb.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.76,0:10:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to level this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.04,0:10:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What? I thought you said you needed to get out of here!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.48,0:10:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Not until I destroy it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.00,0:11:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What fun! How I wish I could have had a ringside seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.26,0:11:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You've had adventures fit for a Hollywood hero!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.72,0:11:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Believe me, I'm no hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.76,0:11:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you really intend to do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.54,0:11:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't like it, leave!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.90,0:11:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Quit the jokes! As I believe you know, I'm quite ill!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.50,0:11:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.06,0:11:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, I've got a ringside seat to one hell of a spectacle.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.90,0:11:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,No way am I bowing out!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.92,0:11:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Then lend me a hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.90,0:11:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.06,0:11:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all I have to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.98,0:11:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn! Another one?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.80,0:11:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so hard to find good help.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.96,0:11:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Consider yourself a sacrificial lamb.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.48,0:11:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.64,0:12:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Your actions are in violation of Clock Tower law against revealing the secrets of magecraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.80,0:12:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't let this pass!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.32,0:12:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, well, what have we here?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.98,0:12:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You're even duller than I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.74,0:12:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You wriggle out of the trap and come running \Nto the hunter to be caught again?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.50,0:12:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,By my Mystic Eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.02,0:12:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, this suits me just fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.98,0:12:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Your magic circuits are thoroughly third-rate,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.34,0:12:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,but I imagine they'll be adequate kindling for my atelier.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.72,0:12:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be sure not to waste a single one.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.18,0:12:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Third-rate? Well, excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.54,0:12:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But then, that makes two of us, \Ndoesn't it, my dear senior?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.00,0:12:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The Mystic Eyes I possess are invulnerable.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.08,0:12:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,With those, and the relics of Iskandar soon to be within my grasp,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.64,0:12:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the Clock Tower itself will quiver before me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.82,0:12:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me guess. You want to get even with the Clock Tower for ignoring your talent, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.24,0:12:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.58,0:12:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.96,0:12:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I've seen all these spells before.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.52,0:12:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But London and Babylon are nothing alike. Everything from the leylines on up is different.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.68,0:12:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You're in way over your head.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.96,0:12:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You bastard! What could you possibly understand about my magecraft?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.46,0:13:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I understand!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.88,0:13:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I know what it's really like when magi fight one another to the death!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.28,0:13:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That'll do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.04,0:13:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The terror, and the agony—\Nof which I'll be sure to teach you!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.32,0:13:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What have you done?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.12,0:13:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, not much. I merely disrupted the leylines,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.16,0:13:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,awakening the evil spirits that sleep here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.42,0:13:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Your repertoire is but a collection of magic tricks—
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.54,0:13:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,a pale imitation of what the Lords can accomplish.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.96,0:13:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Overlook the slightest flaw, and this is the result.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.26,0:14:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I still have my Mystic Eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.00,0:14:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,In a magus-to-magus fight—
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.04,0:14:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You witless clod!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.69,0:14:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,When did I ever say a magus had to defeat another magus in battle to win?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.16,0:14:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.18,0:14:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,What's eatin' you, Waver?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.68,0:14:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.50,0:14:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,This is all I have to pay you back with.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.72,0:14:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I have none of the amusing stories I promised you, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.18,0:14:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm truly a powerless fool, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.80,0:15:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,There's still something I want to do, \Nno matter what it takes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.78,0:15:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.76,0:15:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.44,0:15:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Please lend me more money!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.20,0:15:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to buy back the El-Melloi Classroom that was lost along with my mentor.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.12,0:15:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever for?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.46,0:15:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't stop thinking about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.66,0:15:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I really am...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.36,0:15:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,responsible for his death.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.38,0:15:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't offer any collateral or guarantee.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.18,0:15:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm begging you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.16,0:15:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds good to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.72,0:15:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,With no collateral or guarantee, there's only one thing that would move me to lend you the money.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.00,0:15:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Name it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.26,0:15:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Our friendship!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.64,0:15:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to be the best of friends, Waver!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.96,0:15:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you saying?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.10,0:15:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't this strike you as slightly odd?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.72,0:15:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing odd about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.74,0:15:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel tremendously moved by your words!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.00,0:15:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So the money is yours!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.24,0:15:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Take as long as you need to repay it. \NWe're best friends, after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.12,0:16:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm begging you! Not down my shirt!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.44,0:16:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And there you have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.02,0:16:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.08,0:16:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And in the three years since, you secured the continued operation of the El-Melloi Classroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.44,0:16:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only that, but its success.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.30,0:16:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Spare me the sarcasm, would you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.66,0:16:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You know as well as I do that I'm barely scraping by in maintaining it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.72,0:16:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Leaving the particulars aside, the fact remains that you've allowed the El-Melloi Classroom to survive,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.78,0:16:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,even surrounded on all sides by those \Nopportunistic Clock Tower goblins.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.48,0:16:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What you've accomplished \Nis nothing short of a miracle.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.16,0:16:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Which brings us back to my first question.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.44,0:16:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Do tell me, Waver Velvet.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.50,0:16:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What could have possibly \Nmoved you so deeply
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.57,0:16:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that you'd devote such effort to keeping that classroom going?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.24,0:17:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The one who killed your uncle, Lord El-Melloi,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.62,0:17:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and my mentor, Kayneth, was me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.34,0:17:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,He died because of my own \Nreckless and thoughtless acts.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.88,0:17:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,My relationship with my master was far from amicable.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.72,0:17:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Nor did he hold me in high esteem.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.46,0:17:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But I can't deny that his class \Nshaped me into the magus I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.36,0:17:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I cannot deprive its future students of the opportunities it gave me
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.36,0:17:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,when I was the one seated in that lecture hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.98,0:17:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, do excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.76,0:17:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't expecting such integrity from the likes of you! You've caught me off guard.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.10,0:17:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You do have a point, though. If you hadn't stolen that relic of Iskandar from him,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.00,0:17:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,perhaps my elder brother \Nwould have lived a touch longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.12,0:17:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.10,0:17:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't use it to its full potential.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.22,0:18:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't fit to master the King of Conquerors.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.74,0:18:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I acknowledge the wrong I've done.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.66,0:18:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I only beg you to spare my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.98,0:18:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh ho?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.08,0:18:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't this where you say something like, \N"If this is not enough, then take my life also"?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.68,0:18:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,There are things I still must accomplish.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.72,0:18:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,In the name of my king.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.76,0:18:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well! As long as I have you here,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.80,0:18:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I may as well exploit your guilt \Nto make as many demands as I please.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.86,0:18:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The El-Melloi faction is rather deep in debt at the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.22,0:18:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The money we owe would be enough to fund a Hollywood blockbuster.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.08,0:18:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So you intend to pass that debt on to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.56,0:18:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.34,0:18:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Answering to our creditors is just one of the responsibilities that comes with the name.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.88,0:18:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.90,0:18:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you serious?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.42,0:18:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think I'd take on a crushing debt as a joke?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.78,0:18:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I-In that case, the second condition!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.48,0:18:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,What now?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.36,0:19:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I trust you've heard that my elder brother's magic crest—
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.84,0:19:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the original magic crest of the El-Melloi line—\Nwas nearly lost. We barely recovered a tenth of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.24,0:19:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I had. The essence of who he was as a magus was almost completely destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.18,0:19:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Even if our house Tuner worked at it day and night,\N it would take at least three more generations to restore.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.04,0:19:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,At this rate, our line is done for.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.88,0:19:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Understood. I'll take care of it somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.14,0:19:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.94,0:19:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you quite sure? Aren't you agreeing \Nto these terms with far too little resistance?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.54,0:19:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you come back from the Holy Grail War \Nwith worms in your brain?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.52,0:19:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,My gray matter is perfectly sound! \NI said I'd assume responsibility, and I mean it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.08,0:19:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.92,0:19:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Then let's get to the heart of the matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.96,0:19:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what the title of Lord entails.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.14,0:19:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The highest rank a magus can obtain, and a seat on the council ruling the Mage's Association.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.70,0:19:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.48,0:20:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. To the El-Melloi faction, retaining the position of Lord is absolutely necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.20,0:20:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Without the power it grants to expel another Lord,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.28,0:20:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll swiftly find yourself outside the Clock Tower's inner circle.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.18,0:20:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been chosen as the head \Nof the family for the time being,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.40,0:20:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,but I'm obviously too young to take on the title.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.88,0:20:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'd like you to keep the seat of Lord warm for me until I come of age.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.34,0:20:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't mind, but what exactly would you have me do?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.94,0:20:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Until I'm of age, you are to undertake \Nall work that the position of Lord entails.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.62,0:20:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute! You mean—
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.54,0:20:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I certainly do!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.54,0:20:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Playing diplomatic chess with the other Lords is sure to be a terrible bore, but I'll be counting on you,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.98,0:20:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the new Lord El-Melloi.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.00,0:20:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Or perhaps I should call you...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.28,0:20:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,my dearly beloved
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.98,0:20:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,elder brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.92,0:21:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm to become my master Kayneth's successor?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.50,0:21:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I have one condition of my own.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.52,0:21:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.18,0:21:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Please add "II" to "Lord El-Melloi."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.90,0:21:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,My master is the only one worthy of the original.\NThe name is too heavy a burden for me to bear.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.88,0:21:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And here I was certain you despised my brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.92,0:21:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Personally, I'm not fond of him, even now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.92,0:21:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But as a magus, I deeply respect him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.68,0:21:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And most of all,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.26,0:21:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I have someone I must follow after!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.22,0:21:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That's right.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.22,0:21:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Even though the Holy Grail War is over,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.56,0:22:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}as absurd as it is, life goes on.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.96,0:22:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}So as long as I draw breath,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.58,0:22:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I must struggle to survive.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.63,0:22:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Until the day I reach the place you longed to see,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.51,0:22:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}the furthest ocean!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.25,0:22:41.27,Default,chptr,0,0,0,,{Epilogue}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.62,0:22:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Master! You've returned!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.54,0:22:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.64,0:22:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The fallout from the Izelma business is finally over.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.54,0:22:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That is gladdening to hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.32,0:23:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You have a visitor waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.02,0:23:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That can only be them.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.66,0:23:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome home, my very best friend!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.68,0:23:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,More trouble for me to deal with, I take it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.98,0:23:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, dear brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.44,0:23:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a case for you that will bring you \None step closer to paying off your debt.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.28,0:23:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I guarantee it'll be worth your while!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.26,0:23:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.30,0:23:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What sort of a case is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.50,0:23:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,A supremely difficult one, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.54,0:23:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,More than fit for Lord El-Melloi II.
